        <div id="rules">
            <button id="close-rules-button">Ã—</button>
            <div id="rules-content">
                <h1>Rules</h1>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        The goal of the game is to reach <i>10000</i> points.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        <i>Ones</i> and <i>Fives</i> are the only dice 
                        worth anything on their own, being worth <i>100</i> 
                        and <i>50</i> respectively.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        Three of any kind of dice (on the same roll) are worth <i>100 x [face value 
                        of dice]</i>. For example, three <i>Fours</i> would be worth 
                        <i>400</i> points. Three <i>Ones</i> are worth <i>1000</i> points. 
                        For each extra dice rolled on the same turn, multiply the last value by 2. 
                        For example, four <i>Fours</i> would be worth <i>800</i>, five <i>Fours</i> 
                        would be worth <i>1600</i>, and six <i>Fours</i> would be worth <i>3200</i>.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        If your current score is <i>0</i>, you must score <i>1000</i> points 
                        or higher for your score to be counted. Otherwise, ending your turn will 
                        not grant any points.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        At least one die must be selected to continue your turn. If no valid dice 
                        can be selected, you must end your turn. If no valid dice are currently selected 
                        upon your turn ending, you will lose <i>100</i> points. If going back <i>100</i> 
                        points puts your score below <i>1000</i>, your score drops down to <i>0</i>.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        If all dice are selected, you must roll again, unless you have rolled 
                        a <i>Straight</i> (1, 2, 3, 4, 5, and 6 all in the same roll), which is worth 
                        <i>1000</i> points.
                    </li>
                    
                    <li>
                        After a player reaches the goal of <i>10000</i> points, all other players have 
                        only one roll to catch up to them. If another player surpasses the other player's score, 
                        that now becomes the goal for the other players. The player with the highest score after 
                        all players have taken their last roll is the winner.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
